2084P0804X	2084P0804X	Allopathic & Osteopathic Physicians	Psychiatry & Neurology	Child & Adolescent Psychiatry	Child & Adolescent Psychiatry is a subspecialty of psychiatry with additional skills and training in the diagnosis and treatment of developmental, behavioral, emotional, and mental disorders of childhood and adolescence.	Source:  The American Board of Psychiatry and Neurology, Inc. [1/1/2007: new definition]	\N	\N	\N	metaTaxonomyCode:2084P0804X	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f
